<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_9dc7b397-080d-4b6a-9e11-b9e0e522e0dc" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>B5F1</sptc><title id="_05b32f2e-9165-4e51-acad-cc28b45489c2">Design and installation</title><archive-num>2019: BF5</archive-num><subclause id="_2faa90c1-47e6-409b-a24e-32e3097d6a63" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_62ef0316-37cd-465b-96e1-c4c9b38431a3">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Water services must be designed and installed so as to operate in a way that avoids the likelihood of contamination of any part of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_4415daba-fb61-47d9-bdda-ce1353a6e8ce" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> supply, and minimises any adverse impact on building occupants, the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_4cf8a3e5-60a5-45d6-917e-0503af18f030" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator’s</xref> infrastructure, property and the environment.</p></subclause></clause>